@CLS@

@X09<@X0EC@X09@X09>@X03@X03omment   Comment to the Sysop.  This allows you to send a private
            mail message @X0E(@X0Cup to 99 lines@X0E)@X03 to the Sysop.  As this is
            a private message, it may only be viewed by the Sysop.

            This command is very similar to entering a mail message.
            Messages are entered via the full-screen Visual Editor.
            Visual Editor Help is available by pressing @X09<@X0ECTRL@X09>@X03+@X09<@X0EZ@X09>@X03.
            To exit the Visual Editor, simply press the @X09<@X0EESC@X09>@X03 key.
            Upon exiting the Visual Editor, two available options
            are:

              @X09<@X0ES@X09>@X03ave  the Message   @X0E(@X0Cthis is the typical response@X0E)@X03
              @X09<@X0EA@X09>@X03bort the Message   @X0E(@X0Cmail message is not saved@X0E)@X03


Subtopics:  @X09<@X0EA@X09@X09>@X03@X0B - Advanced_Topic

~

:C A
@CLS@
@X03
Advanced_Topic - Entering Message Files via ASCII Upload.

            If you have a lengthy message, you are a poor typist, or
            you pay exorbitant long distant fees, you can type up the
            Message File offline and enter it via ASCII Upload.

            To do this, enter the @X09<@X0EC@X09>@X03omment command and message subject.
            After entering the Visual Editor, simply execute an ASCII
            Upload with your Telecomm package @X0E(@X0C@X09<@X0EPgUp@X09>@X03 if using Telix.@X0E)@X03
            Exit the Visual Editor via @X09<@X0EESC@X09>@X03 and @X09<@X0ES@X09>@X03ave the Message.

            NOTES:  You may not use a Word Processor @X0E(@X0CWord Perfect,
                    etc.@X0E)@X03 to Type the Message File.  You MUST use a
                    standard ASCII Text Editor @X0E(@X0CI recommend Qedit.@X0E)@X03
                    Also, be sure to place the file in your Upload
                    Directory as configured in your TeleComm Package.
