@X09<@X0ED@X09>@X03ownload  Downloading transfers file@X0E(@X0Cs@X0E)@X03 from the BBS System to your
            computer system.

            If you wish to download several files, I suggest entering
            @X09<@X0ED@X09>@X03 with no parameters.  If you just wish to download one or
            two files, you may pass the file names and "stack" either
            file command @X09<@X0ES@X09>@X03tart or command @X09<@X0EG@X09>@X03oodbye to immediately
            begin the transfer.  If you use @X09<@X0ES@X09>@X03 or @X09<@X0EG@X09>@X03 in this manner,
            the system uses Zmodem as the file tranfer protocol.

            If not otherwise entered, a .ZIP file extension is assumed.


