@X09<@X0EFL@X09>@X03ag      Flag file@X0E(@X0Cs@X0E)@X03 for later download.  This allows you to Flag
            the files you wish to download as you encounter them.  This
            saves enormous time and also preserves our forests.  All
            Flagged Files are automatically selected when entering @X09<@X0ED@X09>@X03.
            Wild cards are allowed and an extension of .Zip is assumed.

            Syntax:  FL fname      to FLag file "fname.zip"
                     FL U fname    to UN-FLag a file "fname.zip"
                     FL U *        to UN-FLag all flagged files
                     FL *          to FLag ALL files.  NO, you can't
                                   download them all, but "nice try."

            NOTE:  You lose your Flag List when executing any of:
                   @X09<@X0EU@X09>@X03pload, @X09<@X0EZIPM@X09>@X03, @X09<@X0ETEST@X09>@X03, @X09<@X0EREPACK@X09>@X03, @X09<@X0EG@X09>@X03oodbye.

ALSO SEE =@X09>@X03 @X09<@X0EF@X09>@X03ile Directory    @X0E(@X0Cto view directory & file listings@X0E)@X03
            @X09<@X0EL@X09>@X03ocate File       @X0E(@X0Cto find a particular file name@X0E)@X03
            @X09<@X0EN@X09>@X03ew Files         @X0E(@X0Cto view only newly added files@X0E)@X03
            @X09<@X0EZ@X09>@X03ippy Search      @X0E(@X0Cto do a keyword search for files@X0E)@X03
