@X09<@X0EHO@X09>@X03tkeys   Enable the HOtkey function for command input.  This provides
            instant response for most commands @X0E(@X0Cno @X09<@X0EENTER@X09>@X03 key needed.@X0E)@X03

            This is one of those features that you either "Love" or
            you "Hate."  The Sysop "HATES" it.  If you aren't familiar
            with ProDoor commands, I highly recommend NOT enabling the
            HOtkey feature.  If you are HOT on this feature, a good
            time to enable it is after you feel comfortable in @X09<@X0EX@X09>@X03pert
            mode @X0E(@X0Cno main menu displayed.@X0E)@X03  For this reason, I have
            restricted its use to security level 50 and above.

     NOTES: Some commands do not function properly in this mode.  Trying
              to enter @X09<@X0ECHAT-NO@X09>@X03 dumps you right into the @X09<@X0ECHAT@X09>@X03 channel
              and @X09<@X0EFL@X09>@X03ag Files gives you a @X09<@X0EF@X09>@X03ile Directory.  Cool, huh?
            In HOtkey mode you should use ";" @X0E(@X0Cnot SPACE@X0E)@X03 to "stack" any
              ProDoor commands such as "J;S".  This is due to the fact
              that the Spacebar functions just like the @X09<@X0EENTER@X09>@X03 key.
            AND, be careful with that @X09<@X0EG@X09>@X03 key!  You HAVE been warned!


ALSO SEE =@X09>@X03 HOT_2_TROT         @X09<@X0Egrin@X09>@X03

